comment.author: 51979177@N02
comment._content: Guess parked here for possible future reference...per AWM records, possibly Lt. George Ernest Rodney Brown (b.1908, Croydon, UK), who served in the RANVR (volunteer reserve) during WW2...this chap looks to be in his early 20s...and the pic looks to have been taken in the 1920s...if this is Brown, then presumably he was in the RAN or RANVR at the time this pic was taken.
